content.description: A tall boulder with a horizontal crack running across the length of it about halfway up. Start from the big jug in the center and head straight up. Gain the crack and then make a big reach to the lip. Probably more like v2-ish if you head left at the crack.
content.location: On the climber's left-side of the Warm Up boulder.

content.description: Start on head high crimps as for The Method Left. Continue up and right onto a good crimp, and continue to a cruxy top out. Spicy for the grade, better of the two Methods. For the line see beta picture for Method Left.
content.protection: 1 pad and a spotter or two pads should suffice. Top-out crux might be a bit spooky with less.
content.location: Same start as Method Left. On the warm up boulder, which is a long boulder visible from the approach trail after about a ten minute hike.

content.description: Start from good full pad head high crimps and move up and left to the mantel topout of Gymania. Good pulling on incut edges.
content.location: On the warm up boulder, just to the right of Gymania. The warm up boulder is the long boulder visible from the trail after about 10 minutes of hiking uphill with a carpet of moss on the left half. Ditch Witch cuts through this moss.

content.description: Classic stiff lowball sit start. Begin sit start on obvious ledge to the left of a tree. Big move out left to an obvious small incut crimp, and then top out on worse crimps. Original Kelly guidebook gave it V5. Seems a bit stiff for that grade.
content.location: Just off of the main trail leading past the warmup boulder and heading towards the Beckey Problem. When you see the warm up boulder, follow the trail for another minute, and look for a short boulder with a roof on the left of the trail heading up. This problem will be on the right side of the boulder.

content.description: Make your way up some pretty full pad edges on a vertical face to a topout mantel. Good finger warmup for the other stuff in the area.
content.location: On the warmup boulder, directly right of Ditch Witch. The warmup boulder is a long boulder visible from the trail after about 10 minutes uphill. Recognizable by a large carpet of moss on the boulder.

content.description: A juggy crack that forms good loaf jugs cutting through a carpet of moss. The crack peters out towards the top leading to a crux topout. Kelly's book gives it 1 star... I think it's quite good and deserves more.
content.protection: One pad, and a spotter to move the pad, or two pads seems fine
content.location: On the warmup boulder visible from the trail. 10 minutes or so uphill from the trail head. The warmup boulder is a long boulder with a large visible carpet of moss.

content.description: This climb is almost an eliminate. Starting at Gymania, step high left and reeeeeach to a tiny little quarter pad crimp. One more good crimp and you'll be right at the end of Ditch Witch. Video in comments for reference/beta.
content.location: Find the Warm-Up boulder. This line doesn't pop out like any of the others and climbs directly up the center of the blankest part of the face between Ditch Witch and Gymania.

content.description: Start on the left corner of the warm up wall on a low flake jug and climb up and left through a cool rounded pinch and out the roof on crimps to a full value topout sequence.
content.location: Left end of warm up wall
